# labspace/labspace.yaml — Docker AI Governance
# Same labspace-infra schema as labspace-sbx (generated from labspace-starter).

title: Docker AI Governance — Hands-on
description: |
  Hands-on workshop covering the three pillars of Docker AI Governance:
  Sandbox Policies, MCP Tool Governance, and Audit & Visibility.
  Single-terminal model: ttyd binds to your Mac shell, sbx and docker mcp
  are ready to use on the right panel.

author: Ajeet Singh Raina <ajeetraina@docker.com>
duration: 60m

sections:
  - id: 00-setup
    title: Setup — Tell us about your org
    file: content/00-setup.md

  - id: 01-introduction
    title: Introduction — The Three Pillars
    file: content/01-introduction.md

  - id: 02-horror-stories
    title: Horror Stories — An Agent With No Boundaries
    file: content/02-horror-stories.md

  - id: 03-sandbox-policies
    title: Pillar 1 — Sandbox Policies (Local)
    file: content/03-sandbox-policies.md

  - id: 04-blast-radius
    title: Pillar 1 — Blast Radius Test
    file: content/04-blast-radius.md

  - id: 05-org-governance
    title: Org Governance Walkthrough
    file: content/05-org-governance.md

  - id: 06-mcp-tool-governance
    title: Pillar 2 — MCP Tool Governance
    file: content/06-mcp-tool-governance.md

  - id: 07-audit-visibility
    title: Pillar 3 — Audit & Visibility
    file: content/07-audit-visibility.md

  - id: 08-bosch-scenarios
    title: Bosch Scenarios — Per-Vertical Mapping
    file: content/08-bosch-scenarios.md

  - id: 99-validation
    title: Validation checklist (facilitators)
    file: content/99-validation-checklist.md
